 authorization2star  aThere is increasing interest in the use of learning outcomes in postsecondary education, and deliberations have surfaced with regard to their potential to serve as a tool for advancing credit transfer. Learning Outcomes, Academic Credit, and Student Mobility assesses the conceptual foundations, assumptions, and implications of using learning outcomes for the purposes of postsecondary credit transfer and student mobility. Through a critical review of current approaches to the use of learning outcomes across national and international jurisdictions, scholars and practitioners in postsecondary education provide a multivalent examination of their potential impacts in the unique context of Ontario and recommend future directions for the system. The collected works are the culmination of a multi-year study entitled Learning Outcomes for Transfer, funded by the Ontario Council on Articulation and Transfer. Contributions are authored by prominent international scholars across countries with significant outcomes-based experience and education reforms (South Africa, the United States, Australia, Europe, and the United Kingdom) and an Ontario research consortium comprising college and university experts working to advance student pathways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCompetency-based education. 0aSchool credits. 0aStudents, Transfer of. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAllais, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArnold, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArnold, Christine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBorin, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBragg, Debra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBridge, Jean,